# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: andrelton-simmons
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:andrelton-simmons/2010-major-league-baseball-draft] The **2010 Major League Baseball draft** was held on June 7–9, 2010 at the MLB Network Studios in Secaucus, New Jersey.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2010-major-league-baseball-draft] The draft order was determined based on the 2009 MLB standings, with the worst team picking first.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2010-major-league-baseball-draft] The "sandwich picks" after the first round are compensation for losses of free agents during the 2009–10 offseason.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The **2012 Major League Baseball season** began on April 5, 2012 because during the MLB Spring Training it was the first of a two-game series between the Seattle Mariners and the Oakland Athletics at the Tokyo Dome in Japan.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] On November 22, 2011, a new contract between Major League Baseball and its players union was ratified, and as a result, an expanded playoff format adding two clubs would be adopted no later than 2013 according to the new Collective Bargaining Agreement.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The new format of the 2012 postseason used the 1 game series of the Wild Card round of the format for the 2012 postseason only.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The restriction against divisional rivals playing against each other in the Division Series round that had existed in previous years was eliminated, as the Baltimore Orioles and New York Yankees squared off in one of the best-of-five LDS in the American League.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] On April 4, 2012, it was the last day of the MLB Spring Training and ended with the new Marlins Park, as the newly renamed Miami Marlins hosted the defending World Series champion St.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The regular season ended on Wednesday, October 3, 2012.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The entire master schedule was released on September 14, 2011.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Major League Baseball postseason was expanded to include a second wild card team in each league beginning in the 2012 season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The season marked the last for the Houston Astros as a member of the National League.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Following the sale to new owner Jim Crane, the Astros agreed to move to the American League effective in the 2013 season, and would be assigned to the American League West, joining their in-state rivals, the Texas Rangers.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Major League Baseball All-Star Game's 83rd edition was held on July 10, 2012 at Kauffman Stadium in Kansas City, Missouri, with the National League winning the All-Star Game for the third consecutive year in an 8–0 shutout of the American League.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] With the win, the National League champion earned home field advantage for the World Series, which began on October 24, 2012 and ended on October 28, 2012 when the San Francisco Giants swept the Detroit Tigers.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Civil Rights Game was held on August 18, 2012 at Turner Field, as the Los Angeles Dodgers beat the host Atlanta Braves, 6–2.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The following managers were hired for the 2012 season after the former manager retired from baseball.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p01] At the end of the 2011 season, the following teams made replacements to their managers.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Five teams have made wholesale changes to their uniforms in 2012, while a sixth has new road uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Two other teams added alternate uniforms to their existing set.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The San Diego Padres were the first team to announce changes to their logos and uniform set on November 9.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The new primary features the "SD" cap logo inside a navy circle with the words "San Diego Padres Baseball Club" encircling it.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The "swinging friar" logo was also revived, albeit in the current colors.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Another secondary logo features the Padres script from last season below the depiction of Petco Park in sand and above the year of establishment; a blue and white version is used on the away and alternate uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The front of the home uniform remains the same, except that the sand trim in "Padres" is now in trim instead of a drop shadow and the addition of navy piping.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Originally they'll use the sand Petco patch on the left sleeve, but upon unveiling the uniforms, the "swinging friar" patch was placed instead.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The road uniforms now feature "San Diego" in an arched position with navy piping.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The alternate blue uniforms feature the "SD" cap logo on the left chest with white piping.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] All three uniforms now feature the block numerals on the reverse side.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The digital camouflage uniforms were retained, save for the change to block numerals.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The caps with the sand "SD" were retired.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Marlins unveiled their changes on November 11, 2011, as the team was rebranded as the Miami Marlins, complete with a new logo featuring a stylized Marlin jumping over an art deco colored "M" in coral, yellow and blue.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] "MIAMI" will grace the primary white uniform, and there will be an orange home alternate which feature the team name, while the black alt had been reduced to road alternate jersey.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The black cap is used for the regular home, away and black alternates, while the orange cap is paired with the orange alternates.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Marlins become the second team to use the city (or state) name on the home uniforms, after the Texas Rangers.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] November 15 saw the Baltimore Orioles redesign their road and home uniform sets and returned to a version of the cartoon logo used from the mid-1960s to 1988.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The home caps are white in front and black on the back with an orange bill, while the away caps will be all black with an orange bill, both featuring the cartoon bird.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They also unveiled a modernized version of the orange alternate uniforms last worn in 1992, and were worn on select home games, but retained the black alternate uniforms paired with the black and orange cap with the "O's" script.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As part of their golden anniversary season, the New York Mets modified their home and road uniforms to resemble the style worn in 1962, having their unveiling November 16.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In addition, the black alternate jersey (which will be worn occasionally on the road in 2012) is being phased out, to be replaced by a blue alternate starting in 2013.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The solid black cap with the blue/white/orange crest will also be retained for one more season, to be worn only with the black alternate jersey.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The black cap with blue bill and blue/orange crest has been eliminated.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In addition, the Mets have removed the color black from their batting-practice jerseys and caps; both will be blue with orange lettering/logos outlined in white.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Toronto Blue Jays unveiled new uniforms on November 18, returning to a variation of their vintage logo used from 1977 through 1996.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The new logo is similar to the original used from 1977–96, with a few exceptions: a more prominent maple leaf, a sleeker-looking blue jay, serifed modern lettering on the team name, and a split-line blue circle enclosing the logo.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The new uniforms are similarly based on the set used from 1989–96; a white home uniform with "Blue Jays", a grey road uniform with "Toronto", and a blue alternate uniform with "Blue Jays".
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The team/city name is arched above the secondary logo of the blue jay with the maple leaf, sans the baseball, situated on the left side.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The secondary logo is also placed in the blue cap.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The uniforms use the breathable double-knit polyester fabric, claiming the previously lighter Climate Base fabric became too heavy, once players began to sweat.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Colorado Rockies replaced their purple road pinstripes with a more traditional solid gray uniform which was unveiled at RockiesFest in Denver in January 2012.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The San Francisco Giants and Atlanta Braves added alternate uniforms to their set.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Giants wear a Sunday road game grey alternate based on the road uniforms they wore during their 1989 World Series run, with the interlocking 'SF' logo on the left chest and black neck-hoop piping.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The black piping was also incorporated into the team's normal road gray uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Braves unveiled a cream (heritage white) home alternates based on the uniforms worn in their first season in Atlanta.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The uniform has the 'Braves' wordmark without the tomahawk with the uniform number below on the left chest and navy piping.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The sleeves have a logo commemorating the Braves franchise's first season in 1876.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] A new, slightly altered Los Angeles Dodgers logo made its way to the Dodgers dugout wall at Dodger Stadium and for their "Social September" promotion in September 2011.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The baseball and flight lines have been thickened, while the "o" in the script "Dodgers" no longer has a line on the bottom left.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The home uniform script continues to use the previous script, though.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] After reviving the Northwest Green jerseys at home, the Seattle Mariners brought back their navy with teal bill caps, last worn in 2002, for Monday and Friday home contests.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Also, their navy road alternate will now have "SEATTLE" on the jersey front.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Royals unveiled minor tweaks to their light blue home alternate jersey, with all numbers and lettering now white with royal trim, and a revamped away uniform (changed to a darker blue-gray color and a revamped "Kansas City" script).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In addition, the team has dropped their light blue caps.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cleveland Indians made minor tweaks to the home and alternate uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The white home uniform features navy collar piping and the 'Indians' script in red and navy trim, removing the white inner trim as well as the navy piping on the button lines.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The navy alternate features gray collar piping and the 'Indians' script in red and white trim, removing the navy inner trim as well as the grey piping on the button lines.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim revert to the silver halo after changing it to gold the previous year.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They also added a sleeve patch that says 'Angels Baseball' with the foundation year (1961) separated by the current logo in between.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The logo is wrapped in a red, navy and silver circle.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] This patch will be placed on all uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As part of their 40th anniversary in Arlington, the Texas Rangers will wear replicas of the four different uniforms they have worn throughout the team's history, the most notable of which are the two uniforms worn during the ownership of then-future president of the United States George W.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As part of their 50th anniversary, the Astros will wear throwbacks throughout the season, including a game with Colt .45s uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Red Sox and the Yankees wore 1912 throwbacks on April 20 to mark the 100th anniversary of Fenway Park.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] It marked only the second time the Yankees have worn throwbacks; the first was in 1996, when they wore New York Black Yankees uniforms at a Negro leagues tribute game in Detroit.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Red Sox and Athletics wore 1936 uniforms on May 2 at Fenway Park.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Twins wore Minneapolis Millers uniforms on June 30 in the second game of a make-up doubleheader against the Royals, who wore the uniforms of the Kansas City Blues.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Nationals wore the uniforms of the 1924 Washington Senators on July 5 against the Giants, who wore the 1924 New York Giants uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Athletics wore the PCL Oakland Oaks uniforms, and the Mariners the Rainiers, on July 8.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Brewers will wear Milwaukee Bears Negro leagues uniforms on July 28.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Diamondbacks will wear a throwback uniform on September 15.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Fans decided online that their 1998 purple uniform will be worn.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The White Sox are wearing 1972 uniforms on Sundays at home this season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Detroit Tigers and Pittsburgh Pirates wore throwback uniforms paying tribute to the Negro league baseball teams Detroit Stars and Pittsburgh Crawfords on May 19.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim and Seattle Mariners wore throwback uniforms of defunct Pacific Coast League teams Los Angeles Angels and Seattle Rainiers on May 26.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Chicago Cubs and San Francisco Giants wore 1912 throwback uniforms on June 2.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Pirates and Royals wore Negro leagues uniforms on June 9 – the Pirates, the Homestead Grays and the Royals, the Kansas City Monarchs.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Tampa Bay Rays wore 'faux-back' 1979 throwback jerseys on June 30 against the Tigers, who also wore throwback jerseys from the same year.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Due to the fact the Rays did not exist as a franchise in 1979, their uniform design was inspired from popular uniform styles such as pullovers and two-tone caps.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The San Diego Padres and New York Mets wore 1989 throwback uniforms on August 3.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Louis Cardinals and Milwaukee Brewers celebrated the 30th anniversary of the 1982 World Series by wearing throwback uniforms on August 4.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cardinals also added a 30th anniversary patch commemorating their World Series victory, exclusive to their throwback uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The next night, the Cardinals wore their road blue uniforms against the Brewers.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cincinnati Reds and Philadelphia Phillies wore throwback uniforms from the 1991 season on August 22.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Ironically, on June 16, 1991, the Reds and Phillies had worn 1957 uniforms at Veterans Stadium.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cardinals wore special uniforms to commemorate their 2011 World Series win on April 13–14.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The 'STL' on the caps was gold with navy trim, while the word 'Cardinals' and the block numbers on the uniforms were gold with navy trim.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Cardinals wore them during the unfurling of their championship flag on April 13, and the presentation of the Commissioner's Trophy and World Series rings on April 14.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] 42 on April 15, the 65th anniversary of Jackie Robinson's MLB debut.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Dodgers wore a Brooklyn-era cap and batting helmet that day, as well.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Pirates and Orioles donned camouflage uniforms during Memorial Day weekend.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Brewers wore an Italian-language batting practice uniform with the word "Birrai" on July 1; their opponents Arizona Diamondbacks ('I D-Backs') also wore Italian-language uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They also wore the Cerveceros uniforms on June 2 against the Pirates ('Piratas').
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Players wore special caps on Memorial Day and Independence Day; the Blue Jays also wore special caps on Canada Day, along with a specialized red uniform.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] This year, a camouflage design was used in lieu of the American and Canadian flags.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In commemoration of the September 11 attacks, all American teams wore caps with the American flag sewn on the left; the Blue Jays sported both the American and Canadian flags on both sides of their caps.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As part of Cinco de Mayo the San Francisco Giants ("Gigantes") and Houston Astros ("Los Astros") wore Spanish-language home uniforms for the game.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] On July 6, the New York Mets ("Los Mets") wore blue Spanish-language jerseys for the game against the Chicago Cubs.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They wore the uniforms again on August 24 against the Astros.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Chicago White Sox wore a variation of their home uniforms on September 7 against the Royals, as part of the "Halfway to St.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The uniform substitutes the traditional black color for green.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Athletics and Diamondbacks wore Spanish-language uniforms in celebration of Mexican Independence Day on September 16, against the Orioles and Giants, respectively.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The A's used their primary home uniform, with "Atléticos" substituting for "Athletics", while the D-Backs used their black alternate uniform, with "Los D-Backs" substituting for the secondary "A" logo.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Florida Marlins vacated Sun Life Stadium at the end of the 2011 season and moved into Marlins Park, which was built on the site of the old Orange Bowl stadium.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The team officially adopted its new name of Miami Marlins on November 11, 2011.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The 2012 season marked the 100th anniversary of the opening of Boston's Fenway Park.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In addition, Dodger Stadium—home of the Los Angeles Dodgers—celebrated its 50th anniversary, and the Baltimore Orioles home, Oriole Park at Camden Yards, also celebrated its 20th anniversary.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The 2012 season also marked the 50th anniversary for the New York Mets and the Houston Astros, but the 51st season for both teams.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Mets began play four years after the Brooklyn Dodgers and New York Giants moved west in 1958, leaving New York City with only one MLB team in the Yankees.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In 1959, New York City attorney William Shea, with support from baseball figures including former Dodgers executive Branch Rickey, proposed a third major league called the Continental League.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Houston and New York City were both among the announced CL cities.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] MLB responded to the threat by placing new franchises in several of these cities, and offered a National League franchise to the owners of the proposed New York CL team, who accepted.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] With Shea's goal of bringing a second major-league team to New York successful, he abandoned the new league, which officially folded in 1960 without ever playing a game.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Mets began play in 1962 at the Giants' former home of the Polo Grounds in Manhattan, moved in 1964 to Shea Stadium (named after the aforementioned William Shea) in Queens, and opened their current home of Citi Field, adjacent to the former Shea Stadium site, in 2009.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Astros were also enfranchised as a direct response to the plans to launch the CL.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They began play in 1962 as the Houston Colt .45s; following a dispute with Colt Firearms over revenues from souvenir sales and licensing fees, the team moved to the Astrodome in 1965 and renamed itself the Astros.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In 2000, they opened their current home, now known as Minute Maid Park.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] In honor of the Astros' 50th anniversary, they donned different throwback uniforms at home on Friday night themed to each decade.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Major League Baseball enters the 6th year of seven-year contracts it signed with its broadcast partners prior to the 2007 season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] This year, Fox will televise the Saturday Game of the Week (which will be shown in prime time each week from May 19 to July 7), the All-Star Game, the National League Championship Series, and the World Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] TBS will show a Sunday Game of the Week, the All-Star Selection Show, all but two Division Series games, the American League Championship Series, and the new wild card elimination games.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] They will also air 10 spring training games, as well as five nationally televised games on Opening Week from April 4–6.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The MLB Network will air a national Game of the Week broadcast every Thursday and the two Division Series games not shown on TBS.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Major League Baseball International will air in syndication the All-Star Game, the ALCS, and the World Series to global markets.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Padres switched from Cox Cable-owned 4SD to a new channel called Fox Sports San Diego, which the Padres also have a minority stake in.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] This is the last season of Houston Astros games on Fox Sports Houston and KTXH.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Starting next season, all games will be on Comcast SportsNet Houston, a new channel the Astros will co-own with the Houston Rockets.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Mid-Atlantic Sports Network (MASN), which broadcasts Orioles and Nationals games, became the latest network to adjust its score box to the 16:9 aspect ratio for high-definition television broadcasts.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The adjustment, which began with Fox Sports' MLB coverage in 2010, was later adopted to other networks, notably ESPN, TBS, Fox Sports Net (except Fox Sports South and some terrestrial television broadcasts produced by Fox Sports), and Root Sports during the 2011 season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As of this season, only the YES Network, New England Sports Network, Comcast SportsNet, SportsNet New York and SportsTime Ohio have yet to move to the newly adjusted high definition broadcast.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] The **2012 National League Wild Card Game** was a play-in game during Major League Baseball's (MLB) 2012 postseason played between the National League's (NL) two wild card teams, the St.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] It was held at Turner Field in Atlanta, on October 5, 2012, at 5:07 p.m.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] The Cardinals won by a 6–3 score and advanced to play the Washington Nationals in the NL Division Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] In addition to being the inaugural NL Wild Card Game, it is notable for being the final game of Chipper Jones’ career, as well as for a controversial infield fly rule call made by umpire Sam Holbrook.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] The Braves started Kris Medlen, who had a 9–0 win–loss record and 0.97 earned run average (ERA) in 12 games started during the 2012 season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] The Cardinals selected Kyle Lohse, who had a 16–3 win–loss record and 2.86 ERA during the season, as their starting pitcher.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Lohse allowed a two-run home run to David Ross in the second inning.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] The Cardinals scored three runs in the fourth inning, in which Chipper Jones committed a throwing error, taking a 3–2 lead.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Medlen allowed a home run to Matt Holliday in the sixth inning.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] After the Cardinals scored two more runs in the top of the seventh inning, the Braves scored one in the bottom of the seventh.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] In the bottom of the eighth inning, Andrelton Simmons hit a fly ball to left field that dropped in between Cardinals shortstop Pete Kozma and left fielder Holliday.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Left field umpire Sam Holbrook called Simmons out, citing the infield fly rule.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Had an infield fly not been called, Simmons would have been credited with a single and Atlanta would have had the bases loaded with one out, trailing 6–3.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Fans littered the field with trash, delaying the game for 19 minutes before a message over the Turner Field public address system advised fans the game was subject to forfeiture by the umpires if the field continued to remain unplayable due to the thrown debris.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Atlanta manager Fredi González announced that the Braves would play the rest of the game under protest.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] The protest was denied shortly after the game by Joe Torre, MLB executive vice president for baseball operations, saying it was a judgment call—which cannot be protested under MLB rules.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Prior to the game, MLB's official Twitter bio included the joke "We don't understand the infield fly rule either".
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] This was quickly removed in light of the controversial call.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Following the controversial play, Cardinals closer Jason Motte entered the game and walked the next batter to load the bases, but then struck out Michael Bourn to end the inning without allowing the Braves to score.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] With two outs and nobody on base in the bottom of the ninth inning, Chipper Jones extended the game with an infield single in his final Major League at-bat.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Freddie Freeman hit a ground rule double, bringing Dan Uggla to bat as the potential tying run.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2012-national-league-wild-card-game] Motte retired Uggla with a groundout to record the save, then both teams rushed off the field after fans resumed throwing debris.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The **2013 World Baseball Classic** (**WBC**) was an international professional baseball competition, held from March 2 to 19, 2013.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] This was the third iteration of the WBC, following the two previous tournaments, held in 2006 and 2009.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Unlike the two previous WBCs, which consisted of the same 16 countries, only the 12 countries that won at least one game in the 2009 WBC were guaranteed a berth in the main tournament.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The automatic qualifiers were Australia, China, Cuba, Dominican Republic, Italy, Japan, Mexico, the Netherlands, Puerto Rico, South Korea, the United States, and Venezuela.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Four qualification brackets were held in late 2012 and respectively won by Canada, Taiwan, Spain, and Brazil, who joined the WBC as the final four teams (the latter two making their WBC debuts).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] As in the 2006 tournament, the first round had a round-robin format, which led to South Korea being eliminated on a run difference tiebreaker.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Venezuela also failed to advance out of a tough group.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The fourth-place teams in each group – Brazil, Australia, Spain, and Mexico – had to participate in the qualifying round in order to return for the 2017 tournament.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The Netherlands improved on its surprising 2009 run by advancing to the semifinal game, as did two-time defending champion Japan.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] However, Japan was eliminated in the semi-finals, losing to Puerto Rico.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] In the final game, the Dominican Republic defeated Puerto Rico to become the first WBC champion from the Western Hemisphere, as well as the first team to complete the WBC with an undefeated record, and the only one to do so until Japan also finished with a perfect record in the 2023 WBC.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Robinson Canó of the Dominican Republic was named the Most Valuable Player of the tournament.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The preparations for the third World Baseball Classic were complicated by a dispute between the Japanese Professional Baseball Players Association (JPBPA), the union for all Nippon Professional Baseball players, and MLB over revenue sharing.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] JPBPA demanded a larger share of advertising and merchandise sponsorship revenue for the tournament, a large chunk of which came from Japanese companies.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] MLB resisted the move in part due to the fact that the World Baseball Classic is a joint production of MLB and the MLB Player's Association, meaning that those two organizations bore the cost of the tournament.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] In July 2012, the JPBPA voted unanimously to boycott the 2013 World Baseball Classic.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The move was interpreted by some news outlets as a non-final decision, aimed at raising the pressure on MLB.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] In September 2012, Japanese players agreed to take part after reaching a compromise with tournament organizers on sharing sponsorship and licensing revenue.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The top three teams from each pool of the first round of the 2009 World Baseball Classic automatically qualified.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] In the first round, each team played the other three teams in its pool once.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Teams were ranked by winning percentage in the first round, with the top two teams in each pool advancing to the second round.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] There, the teams from Pools A and B (in Pool 1) and the teams from Pools C and D (in Pool 2) competed in a double-elimination format.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The top two teams in each pool in the second round entered the four-team single-elimination semifinals.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The four qualifying teams crossed over for the semifinals, with the winner of each pool playing against the runner-up from the other pool.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] In the final, the team with the higher winning percentage of games in the tournament was the home team.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] If the teams competing in the final had identical winning percentages in the tournament, then World Baseball Classic, Inc.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] (WBCI) would conduct a coin flip or draw to determine the home team.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Drawing of lots, conducted by World Baseball Classic, Inc.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The deadline for submitting provisional rosters was January 16, but teams had until February 20 to finalize their roster decisions.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Many Major League Baseball (MLB) players participated.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The United States provisional roster was made up entirely of players from MLB, and champions Dominican Republic provisional roster had only one player not signed to an MLB team in 2013.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The Canadian team had 12 players who appeared in MLB in 2012.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Japan had none and two prominent Japanese MLB players, Yu Darvish and Ichiro Suzuki, chose not to play.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Though five members who competed for the Cuban national team in the 2009 WBC had since defected, the Cuban team was considered strong despite its 2nd-round sacking.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Three members of MLB.com's Top 100 prospect participated: Xander Bogaerts, Eddie Rosario, and Jameson Taillon.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The top 12 teams that participated in the 2009 World Baseball Classic were invited back for the 2013 tournament.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Spain, Canada, Brazil, and Chinese Taipei won their pools of qualification.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Note: Numbers in parentheses indicate positions in the WBSC World Rankings at the time of the tournament.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Organizer WBCI has no interest in the final standings, so IBAF determined final standings for its men's baseball world rankings.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] If a pitcher reached his limit during a plate appearance, he was allowed to finish pitching to the batter but was removed from the game at the end of the plate appearance.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] For purposes of the pitcher use limitation rules, both semifinal games were to be deemed to have been played on the day of the latest semifinal game.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] A mercy rule came into effect when one team led by either 15 runs after five innings, or ten runs after seven innings in the first two rounds.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Instant replay was also available to umpires during the tournament.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] As was introduced in Major League Baseball during the 2008 season, replays were only used to adjudicate on home run decisions, to determine whether the ball was fair or foul, over the fence or not, and the impact of fan interference.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] An alternative version of the IBAF's extra inning rule was also used.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] If after 12 innings the score was still tied, each half inning thereafter would have started with runners on second and first base.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] The runners would have been the eighth and ninth hitters due in that inning respectively.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] For example, if the number five hitter was due to lead off the inning, the number three hitter would have been on second base, and the number four hitter on first base.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] However, this rule was never actually employed in the tournament, as the only extra-inning game in the tournament ended prior to a 13th inning.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] MLB Network was announced as the English-language broadcaster of the 2013 and 2017 tournaments.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] ESPN Deportes provided Spanish-language coverage, and ESPN Radio had audio rights.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2013-world-baseball-classic] Sportsnet was the broadcaster in Canada and ESPN America in United Kingdom, Ireland, and other parts of Europe.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The **2015 Major League Baseball season** began on April 5 with a Sunday night game between the St.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Louis Cardinals and the Chicago Cubs at Wrigley Field, and ended on November 1 with the Kansas City Royals winning the World Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] This was Rob Manfred's first season serving as Commissioner of Baseball.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Major League Baseball All-Star Game's 86th edition was held on Tuesday, July 14 at Great American Ball Park in Cincinnati, Ohio, home of the Cincinnati Reds.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The American League won the game 6–3, to give the American League home-field advantage in the World Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] As was the case in 2014, teams were scheduled to play 19 games against each division opponent for a total of 76 games, and six or seven games against each team from the other two divisions in its league for a total of 66 games.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] All teams were scheduled to play 20 interleague games throughout the season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] For 2015, the interleague matchups were AL East vs.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Since "natural rivalry" matchups will be part of the three-year divisional rotation (for the first time), the schedule format for interleague games was different from previous years.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] During the final day of the regular season, all games were scheduled to start simultaneously at 3:00 p.m.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Eastern Time, reminiscent of the English Premier League's last-day "Survival Sunday" scheduling.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] MLB hoped that this would add excitement and drama during the final day, and also limit teams' ability to rest starters at the last minute based on early game results.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] At the end of the 2014 season, the following teams made replacements to their managers.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The New York Mets changed their home jersey from a cream shade to white and took away the home white alternate jersey.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Minnesota Twins took away the pinstripes from their home jersey and added a gold trim to the "Twins" wordmark.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] A hat was also added highlighting the "Twin Cities" logo in gold.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Pittsburgh Pirates introduced a new camouflage alternate jersey in honor of the U.S.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Military which will be worn during all Thursday home games.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] A new camo-style hat also accompanies this uniform with a black bill and black "Pittsburgh" logo.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Seattle Mariners have added an alternate cream color jersey with blue and yellow, the original colors of the team from 1977–1992.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] An alternate light blue hat with a gold "Seattle" logo will accompany the uniform as well.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The San Francisco Giants have added an alternate black jersey, featuring a new alternate logo depicting the Golden Gate Bridge.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cleveland Indians darkened the shade of navy blue in their caps and jerseys.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Astros and Angels wore 1965 uniforms on April 18 to mark the 50th anniversary of the Astrodome and the 50th anniversary of the renaming of the team to Astros.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds and Cubs wore 1990 uniforms on April 24 to mark the 25th anniversary of the Reds' winning the 1990 World Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Tigers and Indians wore Negro league throwbacks on April 25.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Tigers wore the uniforms of the Detroit Stars, while the Indians wore the uniforms of the Cleveland Buckeyes.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Red Sox wore their 1975 home uniforms on May 5 to mark the 40th anniversary of the club's 1975 AL Championship and trip to the 1975 World Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniforms had the Massachusetts bicentennial patch.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Mariners and Red Sox wore Negro league throwbacks on May 16.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Red Sox wore the uniforms of the Boston Royal Giants, and the Mariners wore the uniforms of the Seattle Steelheads.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cubs and Royals wore 1915 Federal League throwbacks on May 31 (originally, they were supposed to have worn them on May 30, but the game was postponed due to rain).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cubs wore the uniforms of the Chicago Whales, while the Royals wore the uniforms of the Kansas City Packers.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cardinals and Phillies wore 1960s throwbacks on June 19.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cardinals wore 1961 uniforms, which did have the players' numbers on the fronts of the shirts.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Mets and Braves wore Negro league throwbacks on June 20.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Mets wore the uniforms of the Brooklyn Royal Giants, while the Braves wore the uniforms of the 1938 Atlanta Black Crackers.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Red Sox wore their 1975 road uniforms on June 27 against the Rays.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Rays, meanwhile, wore their "fauxback" jerseys, which have a retro feel yet never actually were worn regularly because the franchise did not exist back then.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Athletics wore 1965 Kansas City Athletics uniforms June 27.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Ironically, the Kansas City Royals were their opponents.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Pirates and Brewers wore Negro league throwbacks on July 18.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Pirates wore the uniforms of the Pittsburgh Crawfords, while the Brewers wore the uniforms of the Milwaukee Bears.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Rangers and Astros wore 1980s throwbacks on July 18 as part of a 1980s night promotion at Minute Maid Park.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cardinals and Royals wore 1985 uniforms on July 23 to mark the 30th anniversary of the 1985 World Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] They were supposed to be worn on June 14, but that game was postponed due to rain.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cubs and White Sox wore 1959 uniforms on August 14 in honor of Minnie Miñoso at US Cellular Field.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Each of the White Sox players wore Minoso's number 9.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cubs and Tigers wore 1945 uniforms on August 19 to mark the 70th anniversary of the 1945 World Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The White Sox wore 1976 uniforms on August 27.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Players, coaches, and umpires at all games wore #42 on April 15, the 68th anniversary of Jackie Robinson's debut in the majors.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Giants wore uniforms with gold "Giants" script lettering and numbering on April 18 to celebrate their 2014 World Series title.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] On April 20 (Patriots' Day), the Boston Red Sox wore home white jerseys with "BOSTON" written on the front to mark the second anniversary of the Boston Marathon bombings.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniform also sported the 2013 navy-blue circular patch with a white border on the left shoulder saying "B Strong" (with the red B in the classic font featured on the Red Sox's caps).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Milwaukee Brewers wore their batting practice jerseys as an alternate on April 21.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The front has the Brewers' "M" logo on front, and has gold trim on the side.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Giants wore Spanish-language "Gigantes" uniforms on May 5, Cinco de Mayo.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Orioles wore a special uniform May 11, the first game at Camden Yards with spectators since April 26 due to the riots that took place in the city in April.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniforms were in their home whites, but had their road "Baltimore" script on the front instead of the usual "Orioles".
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds wore camouflage uniforms and caps on May 16 and June 6.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniforms had the "Reds" script on the front, instead of the player's number and the Reds' logo.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] All teams wore camouflage uniforms on May 25, Memorial Day in the United States.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Although Memorial Day is not a legal holiday in Ontario, the Blue Jays wore camouflage.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds wore green caps and uniforms on June 19 as part of a "Shamrock the Ballpark" promotion.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Like the camouflage uniforms, the uniforms had the "Reds" script on the front, instead of the player's number and the Reds' logo; the uniforms have a shamrock on the right sleeve, instead of the Mr.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Blue Jays wore a special uniform on Canada Day.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniform had the Blue Jays wordmark in red, instead of blue.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] They had the Canadian flag on their right sleeve.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Red Sox, their opponent, wore a Canadian flag on their uniform as well.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniform was worn again on August 30.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] All teams wore American flag-themed caps and uniforms on July 4, Independence Day in the United States.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniforms had an American flag on a sleeve.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The logos and players' numbers had stars on them; the caps had a star instead of a baseball on the MLB logo.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Blue Jays wore a jersey with both the U.S. and Canadian flags.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Royals and the Astros wore Spanish-language "Los Reales" and "Los Astros" uniforms on July 25.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Tigers wore Spanish-language "Tigres" uniforms August 8.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniforms were based on the Tigers' 1960 uniforms.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds and the Diamondbacks wore Spanish-language "Los Rojos" and "Los D-backs" uniforms August 21.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Mets wore camouflage uniforms on August 31.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Mariners wore Spanish-language "Marineros" uniforms on September 12.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Astros wore Spanish-language "Los Astros" uniforms on September 27.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] 2015 marks the second year of MLB's eight-year deal with Fox Sports, ESPN, & TBS.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Fox will televise Saturday night games for eight consecutive weeks, leading up to the All Star Game, which will also air on Fox.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Fox will then televise Saturday afternoon games for the last four weeks of the regular season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Fox Sports 1 will televise games on Tuesday nights and Saturdays, both during the afternoon and at night.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] ESPN will televise games on its flagship telecast, Sunday Night Baseball, as well as Monday and Wednesday nights.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] TBS will televise Sunday afternoon games for the last thirteen weeks of the regular season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Fox and ESPN Sunday Night Baseball telecasts will be exclusive; all other national telecasts will be subject to local blackout.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] TBS will televise the National League Wild Card Game, Division Series, and Championship Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] ESPN will televise the American League Wild Card Game, Fox Sports 1 and MLB Network will televise American League Division Series, and Fox and Fox Sports 1 will televise the American League Championship Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The World Series will air exclusively on Fox for the sixteenth consecutive year.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] All postseason games will air on ESPN Radio.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] 2015 was the second year of MLB's eight-year contracts for national broadcasts in Canada.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] As in 2014, when the two Division Series games carried by MLB Network in the U.S. was also exclusive to that channel in Canada despite very limited carriage, Game 3 of the Royals-Astros ALDS was exclusive to MLBN in both countries.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] However Sportsnet aired all games of the Blue Jays-Rangers ALDS in Canada (MLBN carried Game 2 in the United States).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] TSN holds English-language rights to most regular season games in ESPN's U.S. package.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] French-language rights are split between RDS and TVA Sports.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Chicago Cubs opted to re-negotiate their terrestrial television contracts for the 2015 season through 2019, when all the Cubs' television rights contracts will expire, including their cable deal with Comcast SportsNet Chicago.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] WGN-TV will still hold rights to 45 Cubs games per season, and its overflow broadcasts will move to WPWR-TV in place of WCIU-TV.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] WGN will be joined by ABC-owned station WLS-TV, which will now broadcast 25 games per season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The cable network WGN America will no longer carry Chicago White Sox or Chicago Cubs games, as the network has phased out Chicago sports programming as part of its transition towards becoming a nationally focused entertainment network.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] After an absence of over a decade, New York Yankees telecasts will return to WPIX, sharing time with the Mets after WWOR-TV gave up its contract due to the rejection of a contract extension.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Both teams' games on WPIX will still be produced by the YES Network and SportsNet New York respectively.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] ESPN Radio aired its 18th season of national coverage, including Sunday Night Games, Saturday games, Opening Day and holiday games, the All-Star Game, and Home Run Derby, and the entire postseason.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] WBBM became the radio home of the Chicago Cubs starting in April 2015 after long time home WGN gave up the broadcasting rights after 90 years.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] WJZ-FM, for the second time, became the flagship radio station for the Baltimore Orioles.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] WJZ-FM held the rights for the 2009 and 2010 seasons.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2015-major-league-baseball-season-p02] New rules were made to increase the pace of the game.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The **2016 Major League Baseball season** began on April 3, 2016, with a Sunday afternoon matchup between the St.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Louis Cardinals and the Pittsburgh Pirates, the two teams with the best regular-season records in 2015, at PNC Park in Pittsburgh.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The regular season ended on Sunday, October 2, 2016, and the postseason on Wednesday, November 2, 2016, with the Chicago Cubs coming back from a three games to one deficit to defeat the Cleveland Indians in the World Series and win their first championship since 1908.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim shortened their name to its original *Los Angeles Angels*.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Major League Baseball All-Star Game's 87th edition was played on July 12 at Petco Park in San Diego, California, home of the San Diego Padres.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The American League was awarded home-field advantage in the World Series by winning the game 4–2.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] As was the case in 2015, teams were scheduled to play 19 games against each division opponent for a total of 76 games, and six or seven games against each team from the other two divisions in its league for a total of 66 games.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Civil Rights Game was not played this year.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] For 2016, the interleague matchups were to be AL East vs.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] On July 3, 2016, the Atlanta Braves and Miami Marlins played the Fort Bragg Game, a special neutral-site game at Fort Bragg Stadium, a newly constructed field in Fort Bragg, North Carolina, in observance of the Independence Day long weekend.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] It was the first professional, regular-season sporting event held on an active military installation.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] In February 2016, Major League Baseball and the Major League Baseball Players Association agreed to two rule changes.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Arizona Diamondbacks unveiled their new uniform concept for 2016 on December 3, 2015.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The San Diego Padres introduced new uniforms with a blue and yellow color scheme.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The silhouetted batter logo started to appear on the back belt loop of pants.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The New Era flag logo began to appear on all authentic game-used caps, starting with the 2016 postseason.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Milwaukee Brewers added a new alternate uniform with modern colors and a retro design.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Minnesota Twins added a red alternate to their uniform lineup.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Although the Twins announced they would be worn on Fridays, they wore the alternate on April 25 and September 5 (Labor Day), both Monday; they wore it on other days as well.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Philadelphia Phillies added a red alternate that they will wear on mid-week home matinee games.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Pirates wore yellow 1979 throwbacks on home Sunday games, replacing the 1971 throwbacks.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Pirates did wear their 1971 throwbacks on September 7, Roberto Clemente Day.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Mets wore 1986 throwbacks on Sunday home games throughout the season to mark the 30th anniversary of their 1986 World Series title.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Braves and Royals wore Negro leagues throwbacks on May 15.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Braves wore the uniforms of the Atlanta Black Crackers, and the Royals wore the uniforms of the Kansas City Monarchs.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Phillies and Brewers wore 1976 throwbacks from June 3–5.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Phillies' throwbacks included the NL's 100th anniversary logo, while the Brewers didn't because they were an American League team at the time.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Indians and Royals wore 1976 throwbacks on June 4.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The White Sox and Tigers wore Negro leagues throwbacks on June 4.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The White Sox wore the uniforms of the Chicago American Giants, while the Tigers wore the uniforms of the Detroit Stars.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] On June 18, the Giants wore 1978 orange throwbacks, while the Rays wore retro-style "fauxback" jerseys.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds wore 1976 throwbacks on June 24 to mark the 40th anniversary of their 1976 World Series title.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Brewers and Nationals as well as the Braves and Mets wore Negro leagues throwbacks on June 25.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Brewers wore the uniforms of the Milwaukee Bears, while the Nationals honored the Homestead Grays.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Braves wore the uniforms of the Atlanta Black Crackers, and the Mets wore the uniforms of the Brooklyn Royal Giants.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cardinals and Mariners wore 1984 throwbacks on June 25.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cubs and Reds wore 1916 throwbacks on July 6 to mark the 100th anniversary of the Cubs playing at Wrigley Field.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Orioles wore 1966 throwbacks on July 8 to mark the 50th anniversary of the Orioles' 1966 World Series title.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Angels wore 1970s throwbacks on July 15 and 16.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cardinals wore 1956 throwbacks July 23.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cardinals uniforms didn't have the two cardinals and bat, which were only worn that season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Dodgers, their opponent, wore Brooklyn Dodgers caps, but wore their normal road uniform.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Brewers and Pirates wore 1990s throwbacks on July 30.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cubs and Athletics wore 1981 throwbacks on August 6.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Rangers and Astros wore 1986 throwbacks on August 6 to mark the Astros' 30th anniversary of their winning the NL West title.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Padres wore 1998 throwbacks on August 6.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Cardinals wore 1927 throwbacks on August 27 to mark the 90th anniversary of their 1926 World Series title.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Red Sox and Padres wore 1936 throwbacks on September 7 to mark the 80th anniversary of the Padres' debut in the Pacific Coast League.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds and Pirates wore Negro leagues throwbacks on September 9.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds wore the uniforms of the Cincinnati Tigers, which were actually the Reds' road uniforms in the 1930s, while the Pirates wore the uniforms of the Homestead Grays (which the Nationals had worn on June 25 - the Grays called both Pittsburgh and Washington home).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Diamondbacks will wear their 1998–2006 throwbacks on Thursday home games.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Royals wore uniforms with a golden "Royals" script and caps with a golden KC on April 3 and 5 to mark their winning the 2015 World Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Royals then announced they would wear the uniforms on Friday nights for the remainder of the season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Players, coaches, and umpires at all games wore #42 on April 15, the 69th Anniversary of Jackie Robinson's debut in the majors.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Umpires wore a "EA" patch on the left sleeves honoring umpire Emmett Ashford on April 11 for breaking the color barrier for umpires.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] On April 18 (Patriots' Day), the Boston Red Sox wore home white jerseys with "BOSTON" written on the front to mark the three year anniversary of the Boston Marathon bombings.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Red Sox wore a patch on April 21 to mark Earth Day.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The patch is of the two hanging socks surrounded by the recycling symbol.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Red Sox had worn that logo in 2008 and 2009.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds and Giants wore Spanish-language "Los Rojos" and "Gigantes" uniforms respectively on May 5, Cinco de Mayo.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds wore the "Los Rojos" uniforms again on August 13 and September 16 (as part of a Fiesta Rojos promotion).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Teams wore special caps and uniforms with pink lettering on May 8, Mother's Day.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds wore camouflage caps and uniforms on May 21, Armed Forces Day, June 12, August 19 and September 2.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The team's uniforms had the "Reds" script wordmark on the front, rather than the "C" and the Reds and the player's number.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Blue Jays wore a 1970s-era cap May 29 to mark the franchise's 40th season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Teams wore camouflage caps and uniforms May 30, Memorial Day in the United States.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniforms were woodland camouflage, licensed from the US Marine Corps.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Blue Jays wore camouflage of the Canadian forces' CADPAT design, even though Memorial Day is not officially a holiday in Toronto, the province of Ontario, or Canada on the last Monday in May.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Rays wore a special cap on June 17 to mark the Orlando shooting five days earlier.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] They wore the cap of the Orlando Rays, the team's Southern League affiliate from 1999 to 2002.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Both the Rays and Giants, their opponents, wore "ORLANDO" patches.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] Teams wore uniforms with blue lettering on June 19, Father's Day.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Royals and the Astros wore Spanish-language "Los Reales" and "Los Astros" uniforms on June 25.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Blue Jays wore a red uniform July 1, Canada Day.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Indians, their opponents, wore a Canadian flag on their sleeve.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Blue Jays wore their red uniforms again on August 28.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] All teams wore red, white and blue-themed uniforms on July 4, Independence Day in the United States.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds and Brewers wore Spanish-language "Los Rojos" and "Cerveceros" uniforms August 13.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Mariners wore Spanish-language "Marineros" uniforms September 4.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] All 30 teams wore caps with American flags September 11 to mark the 15th anniversary of the terrorist attacks.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Blue Jays wore a cap with American and Canadian flags.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Reds wore green uniforms on September 18.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniforms had the Reds script wordmark on the front, instead of the C and the player's number.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The uniforms have a shamrock on their right sleeves.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Astros wore orange Spanish-language "Los Astros" uniforms September 25.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Marlins all wore uniforms with José Fernández's name and number 16 on September 26 to honor him.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] This was the Atlanta Braves' final season at Turner Field, where the team played its final regular season game against the Detroit Tigers on October 2, 2016.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] From the 2017 Major League Baseball season onward, the Braves will play home games at SunTrust Park in Cobb County, Georgia.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p01] The Toronto Blue Jays had a full dirt infield installed in Rogers Centre after using sliding pits throughout their history there as well as Exhibition Stadium.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] This was the third year of the current eight-year deals with Fox Sports, ESPN and TBS.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Fox aired eight weeks of baseball on Saturday night leading up to the 2016 Major League Baseball All-Star Game, which also aired on Fox.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Fox then televised Saturday afternoon games for the last four weeks of the regular season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] Fox Sports 1 televised games on Tuesday nights and Saturdays, both during the afternoon and night.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] ESPN televised games on its flagship telecast, Sunday Night Baseball, as well as Monday and Wednesday nights.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] TBS televised Sunday afternoon games for the last 13 weeks of the regular season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] TBS will televise the American League Wild Card Game, Division Series, and Championship Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] ESPN will televise the National League Wild Card Game, Fox Sports 1 and MLB Network will televise the National League Division Series, and Fox Sports 1 will televise the National League Championship Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The World Series will air exclusively on Fox for the 17th consecutive year.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] On April 14, 2016, it was announced that 25 *MLB Network Showcase* games would be broadcast in 4K ultra-high definition exclusively on DirecTV in the 2016 season (subject to local blackout restrictions), beginning April 15.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] On July 25, 2016, Major League Baseball Advanced Media and Twitter reached an agreement which allowed the social media platform to stream one MLB game per week.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The games were blacked out in the local markets of the teams playing.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] On October 5, 2015, Toronto Blue Jays owner Rogers Communications announced that all Blue Jays home games on Sportsnet during the 2016 season would be broadcast in 4K.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] ESPN Radio aired its 19th season of national coverage, including Sunday Night Games, Saturday games, Opening Day and holiday games, the All-Star Game, and Home Run Derby, and the entire postseason.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Chicago White Sox moved from WSCR to Cumulus Media's WLS for the 2016 season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Chicago Cubs concurrently moved to WSCR from its sister station WBBM, per an option in the team's contract with CBS Radio in the event WSCR lost the White Sox.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2016-major-league-baseball-season-p02] The Philadelphia Phillies saw their broadcasts move from AM to FM, going from WPHT to WIP-FM (both also owned by CBS Radio).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The **2017 World Baseball Classic** (**WBC**) was an international professional baseball competition, composed of 16 competing nations, held from March 6 to 22, 2017.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] It was the fourth iteration of the World Baseball Classic.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The first-round hosts were Seoul (South Korea), Tokyo (Japan), Miami (Florida, United States), and Zapopan (Mexico).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The second-round hosts were Tokyo and San Diego (California, United States), and the championship round was played in Los Angeles (California, United States).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Twelve of the sixteen competing nations qualified based on their performance during the first round of the 2013 tournament; the remaining four nations were the winners of four qualification tournaments that took place in February, March, and September 2016.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Two of the four qualifiers, Colombia and Israel, made their first appearance in the WBC, and both secured their positions for the 2023 World Baseball Classic.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The Netherlands, Japan, Puerto Rico, and the United States advanced to the championship round.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Defending champion Dominican Republic was eliminated in the second round.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The United States defeated Puerto Rico to win the championship game, 8–0.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Marcus Stroman was named tournament MVP.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] He made three starts for the U.S. and posted a 2.35 ERA in 151⁄3 total innings, including 6 shutout innings in the championship game.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The top three teams from each pool of the first round of the 2013 World Baseball Classic automatically qualified.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The first and second rounds of the tournament were played in round-robin format, with each team playing each other team in their pool once, as was the case in 2006.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] However, in an effort to reduce the likelihood that a team would be eliminated on statistical tiebreakers, the tournament schedule allowed for a seventh game at each pool-play site.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Pool A of the First Round of the 2017 World Baseball Classic was held at Gocheok Sky Dome, Seoul, South Korea from March 6 to 10, 2017, between Team Israel, the Netherlands, South Korea, and Taiwan.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Prior to the start of the tournament, ESPN considered Team Israel, ranked 41st in the world, to be the biggest underdog in the tournament, referring to them as the "Jamaican bobsled team of the WBC".
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Team Israel (3–0) and Team Netherlands (2–1) qualified for the second round, in Japan.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Israel became the first baseball team to go undefeated in the first round of the WBC's main draw after entering the main draw by winning in a qualifying round.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] In what NBC reported was thought to be the tallest batter-pitcher matchup in baseball history, the Dutch team's 7-foot-1-inch (2.16 m) Loek van Mil walked Israel's 6-foot-8-inch (2.03 m) Nate Freiman.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Israel's catcher, Ryan Lavarnway, was named Pool A MVP, after going 5-for-9 (.556/.692/.889), with four walks, a home run, and three RBIs.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Two-time champion Japan concluded Pool B with a 3–0 record.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Cuba defeated Australia to advance to the second round.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] In the first round, after batting .364, Japanese outfielder Yoshitomo Tsutsugoh was named the Pool B MVP.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] After falling behind 5–0 in the sixth inning, Dominican Republic rallied to defeat the U.S.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] On the last day of the pool, Colombia tied their game against Dominican Republic 3–3 in the eighth on a Jorge Alfaro home run, and had a chance to win in the ninth inning, but Oscar Mercado was called out at home trying to score on a sacrifice fly.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The game continued into extra innings, where Dominican Republic scored 7 runs in the 11th to win and finish the pool undefeated.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The U.S. then took an early lead on Canada, winning 8–0 to claim the second berth in San Diego.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Manny Machado of the Dominican Republic was named MVP for the first-round Pool C bracket of the WBC, after batting .357.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] While Puerto Rico cruised in all three of its games, the fight for the other three places was extremely tight.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Italy scored 5 runs in the bottom of the 9th inning to shock Mexico in the first game, then lost an extra-inning slugfest against Venezuela.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] In the final game, Mexico defeated Venezuela in another slugfest and thought they had scored enough runs to advance on tiebreakers, though this turned out not to be the case.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The first tiebreaker criterion is fewest runs allowed per defensive inning played (RA/IPD) in the games among the tied teams.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Although Mexico allowed the fewest runs in those games (19, to Italy's 20, and Venezuela's 21), Mexico played fewer defensive innings (17, while the other two teams had 19) and thus had the highest average RA/IPD (1.117, to Italy's 1.053 and Venezuela's 1.105).
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] This occurred for two reasons: the Italy-Venezuela game went 10 innings, and Mexico was the road team while losing to Italy.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] In fact, the Mexico-Italy game did go into the bottom of the 9th, in which Italy scored runs that were charged against Mexico but Mexico failed to record an out.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] There was confusion during and after the Mexico-Venezuela game, with an initial calculation showing that Mexico had advanced.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Mexico filed a formal protest of its elimination, but the protest was denied.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] As specified in the rules, Mexico was eliminated by the tiebreaker calculation and a tiebreaker game was played between Italy and Venezuela, which Venezuela won with a 9th-inning rally.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] According to the rules as announced at the time, Mexico's last-place finish would have required it to participate in a qualifying tournament in order to re-qualify for the 2021 World Baseball Classic.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] However, MLB announced in 2020 that the field of teams for the 2021 WBC would be expanded, with all 2017 WBC participants qualifying automatically and four new teams coming from qualifying tournaments.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Undefeated Japan (3–0) and the Netherlands (2–1) advanced to the semi-final round, as Israel (1–2) came in third, and Cuba (0–3) fourth.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Pool F started with Puerto Rico handing the Dominican Republic its first loss since the 2009 World Baseball Classic.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Puerto Rico ended Pool F still undefeated and Venezuela was eliminated, going 0–3.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The final game of the pool was a rematch between the United States and Dominican Republic to advance to the championship round.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The DR took an early 2–0 lead in the first inning, but the United States came back to win 6–3 to eliminate the defending champions.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] The final standings were calculated by the WBSC for inclusion in the WBSC Men's Baseball World Rankings system.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] When the 2017 WBC was played, it was assumed that the field for the following 2021 WBC would remain 16 teams.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] Under the qualification format in use at the time, the bottom four finishers from 2017 (Canada, China, Mexico, and Chinese Taipei) would've been forced to re-qualify for 2021.
[src:andrelton-simmons/2017-world-baseball-classic] However, in January 2020, MLB announced it was expanding the field for the 2021 WBC from 16 teams to 20 and that all 16 participants from 2017 would receive automatic bids for 2021, thus sparing the bottom four nations from relegation to the qualifiers.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Drawing considerable attention for his defensive abilities, Simmons won four Rawlings Gold Glove Awards at shortstop, a Wilson MLB Overall Defensive Player of the Year Award, and six Fielding Bible Awards.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] As of the end of 2019 season, he ranked first in DRS and UZR against all shortstops who played in the stats' respective eras (2003–present for DRS, 2002-present for UZR).
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Simmons played youth baseball alongside fellow Curaçao natives Kenley Jansen and Didi Gregorius; he also played basketball and soccer.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Due to his slight build, Simmons did not draw much attention from MLB scouts until he attended Western Oklahoma State College in Altus, Oklahoma.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] As a freshman at Western Oklahoma State, Simmons hit .472 with seven home runs and 40 runs batted in (RBIs), leading his team to the 2010 National Junior College Athletic Association Division II College World Series.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Simmons was drafted by the Atlanta Braves in the second round of the 2010 Major League Baseball draft out of Western Oklahoma State College.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Prior to the 2012 season, Simmons was the Braves' fourth-best prospect according to *Baseball America*.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] During spring training he competed with Tyler Pastornicky for the Braves starting shortstop job.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On May 30, 2012, the Braves called Simmons up, and he made his Major League debut on June 2 against the Washington Nationals.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] He got his first Major League hit, a double, on June 3.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Simmons was named National League Rookie of the Month for June 2012 after hitting .333 with six doubles, three home runs, and 14 RBIs in June.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] He led all NL rookies in batting average and on-base percentage.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] He also won praise for his outstanding defense.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On July 8, 2012, during a game against the Philadelphia Phillies, Simmons suffered a non-displaced fracture of the fifth metacarpal on his right hand while sliding head-first into second base.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On July 9, he was placed on the 15-day disabled list.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] In the 2012 National League Wild Card Game against the St.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Louis Cardinals, Simmons hit an eighth-inning fly ball to left field that dropped in between Cardinals shortstop Pete Kozma and left fielder Matt Holliday.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Simmons was believed by many to have been entitled to a single, but left field umpire Sam Holbrook cited the infield fly rule and called Simmons out.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Angered Braves fans littered the field with trash, causing a 19-minute delay and a threatened forfeit.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] The Braves lost the game 6–3 and were eliminated.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Simmons had his first full season in 2013, playing in 157 games.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] He finished the 2013 season with the highest Defensive Runs Saved ever recorded in a year and received the Gold Glove, the Fielding Bible Award, and the Rawlings Platinum Glove Award for his defensive work that season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On February 20, 2014, the Atlanta Braves signed Simmons to a seven-year deal worth $58 million.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] At the end of the year, Simmons won the Gold Glove and Fielding Bible awards for his position.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] He had the lowest number of pitches per plate appearance in the major leagues (3.27).
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On November 12, 2015, Simmons, along with catcher José Briceño, was traded to the Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim for Erick Aybar, Sean Newcomb and Chris Ellis.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] In a May 9, 2016, game against the Tampa Bay Rays, Simmons tore the ulnar collateral ligament of his left thumb and was placed on the disabled list.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] For the season, he batted .281/.324/.366, and struck out in only 7.9% of his at bats.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] He received the Fielding Bible Award for the fourth straight year.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] In 2017, Simmons hit .278/.331/.421 with 14 home runs and 69 RBIs, and had the lowest strikeout percentage of all major league baseball players (10.4%).
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Simmons finished 8th in the American League Most Valuable Player voting.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] He received his third Gold Glove Award as well in 2017.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] His Defensive Wins Above Replacement in 2017 was 5.0, third-highest of all time and highest since 1917.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] He also won a Gold Glove for the second consecutive season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] As of 2018, he led the major leagues in career at bats per strikeout (10.32).
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] He was placed on the disabled list on May 21, 2019, with an ankle injury.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On September 22, 2020, Simmons announced he was opting out of the remainder of the 2020 season.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] At the time of his opt-out, Simmons had slashed .297/.346/.356 with no home runs and 10 RBI.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] While he initially attributed the opt-out to concerns relating to the COVID-19 pandemic, Simmons later revealed in February 2021 that he opted-out due to depression and suicidal ideations.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On January 31, 2021, Simmons signed a one-year, $10.5 million contract with the Minnesota Twins.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Simmons finished the 2021 season with a .223 batting average, 3 home runs, 31 RBI, 1 stolen base, and a 57 OPS+, the lowest of his career.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On March 15, 2022, Simmons signed a one-year, $4 million contract with the Chicago Cubs.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] In 34 games for Chicago, he batted .173/.244/.187 with no home runs, 7 RBI, and 4 stolen bases.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Simmons was designated for assignment on August 6, and elected free agency the following day.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On October 23, 2023, Simmons was drafted in the first round by the Mumbai Cobras, with the 8th overall selection, of the Baseball United inaugural draft.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On December 26, 2023, Simmons announced his retirement from professional baseball.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Despite his retirement, on January 13, 2024, Simmons was announced as part of the Curaçao Suns roster that would represent Curaçao in the 2024 Caribbean Series in Miami.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] On January 12, 2025, Simmons came out of retirement and signed with the Dorados de Chihuahua of the Mexican League.
[src:andrelton-simmons/andrelton-simmons] Simmons represented the Netherlands national team at the 2013 World Baseball Classic, 2017 World Baseball Classic., and 2023 World Baseball Classic.
